      {
        "position": 3,
        "title": "Nice Design with Limited Air Flow",
        "text": "This is a really nice pet carrier - actually far nicer than I was expecting, with a lot of small details that are appreciated.This is for pretty small pets, so keep that in mind when ordering. My eight-pound cat is limited in this carrier, and if you have a pet that is really opposed to getting in a carrier, this will be hard to use. If you need this type of carrier for air travel, I would start working early with your pet to get them used to being in it.This bag has an interesting feel to the body of it, soft fabric that isn't fabric in the usual sense. The seams on the whole thing look really well-done, with no loose ends, no jagged lines, no threats of gaping. All faux leather parts are extremely soft to the touch, and the handles feel really secure when lifting the small bag.There is a built-in lead to the bottom of the inside of the carrier, which is a must. I would highly recommend using a harness when taking this type of carrier and securing the animal that way. It prevents them from being spooked and pulling on their neck and offers a firmer base to ensure they stay put.The removable pad is stiff and helps enforce the bottom and keep the entire bag expanded for pet comfort and to avoid the walls of the bag itself from being too soft. If you are planning to carry a cat, I feel the lining inside may be more prone to tears due to their nails, so just keep an eye on that, or for any animal in there.The window on the side panel is a nice touch for their viewing ease or to keep them in a darker environment, which can help calm anxious pets, especially when there's a lot of unknown noise and/or activity all around them. It can snap shut or, when rolled up, snap into the open position with ease.The zippers have little paw pullers on them, which is a cute touch, and the back has a flush pocket to allow for storage of documents related to your pet, like vet records or their boarding pass.The only venting does seem to be along the top panel. This can be good and bad. It's good in that it keeps the bag really firm/reliable and reduces friction/tear points. This can also be a downside, as if this bag is, say, under the seat in front of you on a plane, you have more of a chance of these being pushed into a more narrow position depending on the size of the pet and the position of the bag. It's something to keep in mind if you are using the bag in places that will have more tight/controlled spots for this bag. I've flown with a cat before and had to use a bag about this size to cram her little furry self into it - the area you have to put this bag is going to be small.This is a really cute little bag, but in some ways, I feel it focuses more on design for the owner than on the comfort for the pet. I would be more comfortable using it in confined areas like planes if there were a few more sources of ventilation for the animal, hence the star minus.Also, keep in mind that with the top only being the source of air, that does make it harder for your pet to cool off while in this bag. Keep this in mind and check accordingly on the animal inside.I would have liked to see a bit more ventilation areas concealed in the design of this bag to provide better cross-flow of air and less risk of restricting air flow when using on a plane. It really is a cute little bag for small animals and can be a great way for those wanting to take them on short errands. And that's probably what I would recommend it for, short-haul trips.",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "April 12, 2026",
